      </details>

      <details style="margin-bottom: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-radius: 4px; padding: 1rem;">
        <summary style="font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer;">My GP keeps telling me I am fine but I cannot stop worrying. What do I do?</summary>
        <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem;">This is a very common experience in health anxiety. If medical investigations have not found an explanation for your symptoms or concerns, and your GP is suggesting anxiety may be involved, a referral to a psychologist (via a Mental Health Treatment Plan) is a reasonable next step. You do not have to be convinced that anxiety is the cause to benefit from working with a psychologist — the process involves exploring this collaboratively, not accepting a label.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="margin-bottom: 1rem; border: 1px solid #e0e0e0; border-radius: 4px; padding: 1rem;">
        <summary style="font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer;">Is health anxiety more common now than it used to be?</summary>
